title: Print, "Paper Doll Costume in Pink with Black Lace and Yellow Bodice", 1876–80
medium: Lithograph, brush and watercolor on cream heavy wove paper
description: Pink shell with black lace trim and yellow bodice. Doll holds bouquet of roses in her right hand, and a handkerchief in her left.  Both back and front of dress are represented.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Paper Doll Costume in Pink with Black Lace and Yellow Bodice", 1876–80.
1876–80. Lithograph, brush and watercolor on cream heavy wove paper. Gift of Grace Lincoln Temple. 1937-22-20.
